# Role List Delete Flow:

01. RoleListView.jsp me har record ke saath checkbox diya gaya:
    <input type="checkbox" name="ids" value="<%=bean.getId()%>">

02. User ek ya multiple records select karta hai aur Delete button par click karta hai.

03. Form submit hota hai aur request RoleListCtl ke doPost() method me jati hai.

04. doPost() method me:
    - pageNo aur pageSize request se liye jate hain
    - operation parameter nikala jata hai

05. ids array get kiya jata hai:
    String[] ids = request.getParameterValues("ids");

06. Check kiya jata hai:
    if (OP_DELETE.equalsIgnoreCase(op))

07. Agar ids null nahi hai aur length > 0 hai:
    - ek RoleBean object banaya jata hai (deletebean)

08. for loop chalaya jata hai:
    for (String id : ids)

09. Har id ke liye:
    - deletebean.setId(DataUtility.getInt(id))
    - model.delete(deletebean) call hota hai

10. RoleModel.delete() method me:
    - database connection liya jata hai
    - SQL query execute hoti hai:
        delete from st_role where id = ?

11. pstmt.executeUpdate() call hota hai aur record database se delete ho jata hai.

12. conn.commit() call hota hai aur transaction complete hota hai.

13. Loop complete hone ke baad:
    ServletUtility.setSuccessMessage("Data is deleted successfully", request) set hota hai.

14. Agar user ne koi record select nahi kiya:
    ServletUtility.setErrorMessage("Select at least one record", request) set hota hai.

15. Fir dubara:
    model.search(bean, pageNo, pageSize) call hota hai updated list ke liye.

16. Updated list request me set ki jati hai:
    - setList
    - setPageNo
    - setPageSize
    - setBean

17. ServletUtility.forward(getView(), request, response) call hota hai.

18. Request wapas RoleListView.jsp par forward hoti hai.

19. JSP par updated list show hoti hai jisme deleted records nahi hote.
